translated: Blomberg, Ernst, dentist, Gothenburg, born October 17, 1885 in Timrå, Västernorrland, first child of August B. and Christine Wikström. Married on the 15th of a month in a year ending with "15" to Mary Viktoria Hammarström. Children: Lars-Henrik born in 1916, medical licentiate, Uppsala, Mary-Anne born in 1919, married to Colonel Xavier Sainz, Biarritz, Ragnar born in 1922, studying, and Carl-Otto born in 1925, studying. Graduated from Mogiex. in Sundsvall in 1905, studied dentistry and graduated in 1910, obtained Doctor of Dental Surgery degree from Northwestern University in Chicago in 1911. Practicing in Gothenburg since 1911. Chairman of the Gothenburg Dental Society in 1926. Hobbies: tennis, cycling.
